// DEPRECATED 2026-06-05 — do NOT merge into keybindings.json. No keybinding is needed anymore.
//
// History: 2026-06-03 a `claude-vscode.focus` chord was added to "focus the Claude input" before the
// synthetic Enter on a cold worktree spawn; 2026-06-05 it was upgraded to runCommands[closeSidebar,
// closeAuxiliaryBar, claude-vscode.focus]. BOTH were WRONG — a cascade of compensating hacks:
//   - auto-continue.sh AXRaised the spawned window (raise_task_window), which reset keyboard focus to the
//     window default (the LEFT Explorer / sidebar Claude);
//   - the `claude-vscode.focus` chord then GRABBED the empty sidebar Claude input (it focuses a visible
//     sidebar webview), so the Enter submitted nothing → ABORT.
//
// Root simplification (owner-diagnosed, verified 3/3 live): the URI paste already leaves keyboard focus
// ON the editor Claude input. "Paste, then Enter" — with NO AXRaise and NO focus command — submits
// reliably. auto-continue.sh now uses a bare, front-window-guarded Enter (do_focus=0) on the cold path.
// There is nothing to bind. Kept as a tombstone so a future session does not re-introduce the chord.
[]
